were living at home independently, 68% had returned to work, and only 11% 
reported marked or severe disability. The majority of patients had no problems 
with mobility (75%), personal care (75%), usual activities (66%) or 
pain/discomfort (71%). However, 61% of respondents reported either moderate 
(48%) or severe (13%) anxiety.
CONCLUSIONS: The majority of survivors have good functional and quality of life 
outcomes. Telephone follow-up is feasible in the young adult survivors of 
cardiac arrest; loss to follow-up is common.

