Graphical and demographic synopsis of the captive cohort method for estimating 
population age structure in the wild.

Carey JR(1), Müller HG, Wang JL, Papadopoulos NT, Diamantidis A, Koulousis NA.

Author information:
(1)Department of Entomology, University of California, Davis, CA 95616, USA. 
jrcarey@ucdavis.edu

The purpose of this paper is to complement the literature concerned with the 
captive cohort method for estimating age structure including (1) graphic 
techniques to visualize and thus better understand the underlying life table 
identity in which the age structure of a stationary population equals the 
time-to-death distribution of the individuals within it; (2) re-derive the basic 
